<abstract><t>Flow-based measurement is currently a popular method for traffic monitoring.  To construct a measurement system, an IPFIX mediation device (IPFIX Mediator), which reroutes, filters, aggregates, or modifies Flow information, may help scalability and several other purposes.  This document describes the applicability of an IPFIX Mediator and the problems that the IPFIX Mediator might encounter.</t></abstract>

